results.notes:
Growing abundantly on the undersides of fallen Sabal palmetto fronds. Basidiocarps cupulate; sessile; white; shriveling quickly after being lifted from the forest floor; not connected by a subiculum. All structures inamyloid. Monomitic without clamps. Lacking specialized hairs. Cystidia absent. Basidia 4-sterigmate. Spores apparently hyaline, smooth and thin-walled. Comments: Growing solitary and in shelf-like clusters of fan-shaped pilei; more than 50 fruit bodies on the trunk found.

results.notes:
Fruiting on a fallen Alnus rubra branch.
Fruiting bodies: delicate, very lightweight, flimsy. Consistency like packed wet toilet paper but durable/stretchy.
Hymeniphore: densely wrinkled/folds.
Older specimens exhibiting blue gray/brown tones.
Harvested 3 specimens.
Carefully removed a portion of pore surface/hymenial tissue and mounted in 3% KOH.
Spores: Cylindrical to curved(sausage shaped).
Spores very small.
Basidia: 4 sterigmate.
Dehydrated all specimens thoroughly and bagged for herbarium collection/genetic record.

results.notes:
Fruiting on a fallen Douglas fir branch.
Fruiting bodies: Brain like, clear gelatinous creamy toned-but firm/hard(very unlike Dacrymyces sp).
Harvested 2 specimens.
Carefully removed a small portion of outer tissue and crush mounted on a glass slide in 3% KOH.
Spores: Globose to subglobose with many fused together and attached to long trailing jellyfish tentacle like strands/apiculus like projections.
Size: Very large.
Thoroughly dehydrated both specimens and bagged for herbarium collection/genetic record.
